Mm, I like Kg7 better.  Yes, white ends up with both the f6 & g5 pawns anyway, with Ne8+, Kf7, Nxf6, followed by Kxg5.  But this way white's king sits on a square invisible to white's black bishop, and white must negotiate a series of knight moves to force the king to move.  Plus black's bishop can still protect Pd7, which is preventing the promotion of white's c pawn.
